.TH SHEETS 1 sheets\-VERSION
.SH NAME
sheets \- minimal spreadsheet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sheets
.RB [ \-v ]
.RI [ file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sheets
is a minimal terminal spreadsheet program. It reads and writes CSV
files and supports formulas with cell references.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
prints version information to stdout, then exits.
.SH USAGE
.TP
.B h/j/k/l or arrow keys
navigate between cells.
.TP
.B Enter or e
edit current cell (keep content).
.TP
.B i
edit current cell (clear content).
.TP
.B =
start entering a formula.
.TP
.B x or Delete
delete current cell.
.TP
.B y
yank (copy) current cell.
.TP
.B p
paste yanked cell.
.TP
.B g
go to cell A1.
.TP
.B G
go to last used row.
.TP
.B 0 or Home
go to first column.
.TP
.B $ or End
go to last used column in row.
.TP
.B Tab/Shift-Tab
move right/left.
.TP
.B PgUp/PgDn
scroll page up/down.
.TP
.B Ctrl-S
save file.
.TP
.B :w [file]
save to file.
.TP
.B :q
quit (warns if unsaved).
.TP
.B :q!
quit without saving.
.TP
.B :wq
save and quit.
.TP
.B :<cell>
go to cell (e.g., :B5).
.SH FORMULAS
Cells starting with
.B =
are evaluated as formulas. Supported operations:
.TP
.B +, -, *, /
arithmetic operators.
.TP
.B A1, B2, ...
cell references.
.TP
.B SUM(A1:A10)
sum of range.
.TP
.B AVG(A1:A10)
average of range.
.TP
.B MIN(A1:A10)
minimum of range.
.TP
.B MAX(A1:A10)
maximum of range.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sc (1)
